Overview of RITA settings and usage

RITA's config file is located under /etc/rita/config.yaml, a YAML file with all the parameters to run RITA. So, to test RITA's settings, open up your terminal and then execute the following: 

rita test-config | head -n 10 

If everything went fine and as expected, you should see the same output as the screenshot below.

RITA comes with a detailed usage help message that shows all the parameters you can use within the framework.

Examples and not limited are show-beacons, show-exploded-dns, and html-report. Those parameters will be covered later in the lab. To get the complete list of the parameters, open your terminal, then execute the following:

sudo rita
